article.headline: Gardner-Webb 29, Charleston Southern 25
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. (AP) -- Patrick Hall ran for two touchdowns and Duvaughn Flagler scored on an 11-yard pass from Stan Doolittle with less than five minutes left to give Gardner-Webb a 29-25 win over Charleston Southern on Saturday. Evan Kay added field goals of 23 yards and 39 yards for the Bulldogs (4-4, 2-0 Big South Conference), who rushed for 186 yards on a season-high 45 carries. Hall ran for 100 yards on 13 carries, while Doolittle went 28-17-0 for 200 yards in the air. Sidney Bryant made two short TD passes for the Bucs (3-5, 0-2), including the 5-yard toss to Vernon Huger that gave Charleston Southern a 25-22 lead a few minutes into the fourth quarter. He completed 19 of 29 passes for 146 yards.
